                  <summary>Private letter from Panopolis (modern name: Akhmim), Egypt, written on papyrus. Letter from Ammon, the well-known scholastikos, or lawyer, to someone else whose name begins with Aurelius. Letter concerns a baby. Mentions Panodora and Ammon. Belongs to the archive of Ammon</summary>
